args:
When Jinlorda suddenly appears, the prince
tries to convince him to give up on obtaining
the Dawnshard, but he threatens force instead.
Then the five members of Agito also show up
and challenge the prince and his party.
Detecting several life signatures ahead.\nCaution required.\n▷Someone's coming.◁
It's a group numbering in the dozens.
Likely using the power of metamorphosis.\nWhich means...
All of you can just stop right there.
Ah, the seventh scion and his merry little\nband! How good to finally meet you.
In the flesh! However, I am rather reluctant\nto be identified in any way with that man.
I am Jinlorda, king of the Faerie Kingdom!\nIt's a pleasure to make your acquaintance.
And you are the seventh scion of Alberia,\nand Nedrick's... Mmm, yes. I see.
Ah, and there's little Notte. It fills me with\njoy to see you safely returned home.
Huh? Do you know me, bub?
Yes, although only from having laid eyes\nupon you when you were yet small.
Please permit me to offer my sincerest\napologies regarding my predecessor\nusing you for his own selfish desires.
I am deeply grateful to you for welcoming\na member of my faerie people with open\narms, {player_name}.
You don't have to thank me. Notte's a good\nfriend, and she's always helping us out in\none way or another.
Uh, anybody else here surprised by how\nreasonable this guy is?
Perhaps we might speak on the matter\nwhich Finlorda bade us now.
Of course. Jinlorda, your father has asked\nme to come here and stop you.
Will you renounce your quest to obtain\nthe Dawnshard?
I thank you for coming all the way here\nas an emissary of my dear father.
However, the Sacred Tree has belonged\nto us faeries for generations.
And as I am king of the Faerie Kingdom,\nthe use of anything that may relate to this\ntree is entirely my prerogative.

We will be the ones to determine how the
Dawnshard will be used, and we require
no unsolicited input on the matter.
Return to the city and inform him of this.
Oh, and we have even less interest in your\nopinion on the matter, if that wasn't clear.\nAnd with that, I bid you farewell.
I'm sorry, but I can't simply go back to\nFinlorda and say, ＂Well, I tried.＂
And even if I could, Nedrick is waiting for\nme. I have to defeat him and save my\nsister, no matter what it takes.
Ah, yes. They are indeed just ahead.
However, I do not think your darling sister\nis awaiting your rescue with bated breath.
Of course she's waiting to be rescued,\ndude! Nedrick freaking KIDNAPPED her!
If you were to continue on, you would\ndiscover what she thinks for yourself.
But alas and alack, I cannot permit you\nto pass.
And if you attempt to force your way by,\nyou will come to a most terrible harm.
Do you seek to threaten us, sir?!
Well, I gave you a chance. In that case,\nI will wield the power of metamorphosis\nto eliminate you by force.
Although I think you'll find we aren't the\nonly ones who've taken an interest in you.
OH, COME THE HELL ON! REALLY?!
These guys oughta just get tattoos of my\nface if they miss me so badly...
Be careful, everyone. There's something\nstrange about them.

There's a disparity between the biological
data of the five members of Agito and these
individuals.  ▷They're different from the
ones we've fought so far!◁
So what's up, chump? What'd you do to our\nold Agito pals?
Oh, no, no, no. Neither I nor Nedrick ＂did＂\nanything to them at all. They each made\ntheir own decisions in the matter.
After losing to you, they swore revenge and\nsought to amplify the power of the masks\nthey had been given.

They bolstered their fighting instincts to
the very limits of their control, and as part
of that process limited even their ability
to communicate.
So they can't speak and seek only to\ndestroy us with greater fervor than ever?
I would not spare them any sympathy were\nI in your shoes.
Get ready! This is going to be tough!
